title: Saborio scores in extra time; DC United secures playoff spot
text:
Saborio scores in extra time; DC United secures playoff spot Associated Press 8 hrs ago Â© (AP Photo/Nick Wass D.C. United forward Alvaro Saborio, left, follows through on his kick against Columbus Crew defender Tyson Wahl (2) during the first half of an MLS soccer MATCH, Saturday, Sept. 19, 2015, in Washington. (AP Photo/Nick Wass) WASHINGTON (AP) -- Alvaro Saborio knocked in a loose ball on a free kick in the 92nd minute and D.C. United beat New York City FC 2-1 on a rainy Friday night to secure an Eastern Conference playoff spot.
AdChoices D.C. United (14-12-6) snapped its six-game winless stretch to move into a first-place tie with the New York Red Bulls. NYC FC (10-15-7) had its three-game winning streak stopped.
Frank Lampard opened the scoring in the first minute for the fastest goal in NYC FC's first season. Bill Hamid blocked David Villa's fast-break attempt and Lampard slotted the rebound for his third goal in his last four games.
Fabian Espindola tied it in the 73rd minute. Josh Saunders dove to get a hand on Chris Pontius' shot and Espindola put in the rebound.
Villa sent a ball just over the crossbar in the 41st and rolled one wide of the near post in first-half stoppage time.
